column7: S023 - Cars Order allocation/Round Off is not happening properly, Car allocation is deviating from the expected as per pattern
column47:
In S023 - We are doing Order allocation suppose through various options as below:
E.g.
1. Target Volume Copy By Order Ratio
2. By N month Order Ratio

As per the screen shots attached 
For the Case-1 (1. Target Volume Copy By Order Ratio)
After the pattern execution - expected cars allocation was 9 - but 10 cars are allocated.
Rounding off issue is there - Rounding off should be done as per Limit as well. If Limit is reached the rounding off should not be done for upper limit it seems. Please check.

In Case-2 (2. By N month Order Ratio)

2.If CS=All in Search Criteria, then all CS list should be populated in CS combo of Allocation Support Tool section

column7: S047 Search - OCF/CCF Request Order Quantity - Query Change
column47:
As in the Design Document for Process id : P0007.5:																												
		TABLE																						
			ORDERABLE_END_ITEM_FEATURE_MST																										
			ORDERABLE_SALES_END_ITEM_FEATURE_MST																										
			WEEKLY ORDER TRN																										
			BUYER MST																										
			POR_MST																										
			ORDERABLE SALES END ITEM MST																										
			ORDERABLE END ITEM BUYER MST																										
			ORDERABLE END ITEM SPEC MST																										
		EXTRACTION FIELD																											
			WEEKLY ORDER TRN.POR CD																										
			WEEKLY ORDER TRN.PRODUCTION MONTH																										
			WEEKLY ORDER TRN.PRODUCTION WEEK NO																										
			SUM(WEEKLY ORDER TRN.REQUESTED ORDER QTY)																										
			ORDERABLE_END_ITEM_FEATURE_MST.FEATURE_CD																										
			ORDERABLE_SALES_END_ITEM_FEATURE_MST.FEATURE_CD																										
			ORDERABLE_END_ITEM_FEATURE_MST.OCF_FRAME_CD																										
			ORDERABLE_SALES_END_ITEM_FEATURE_MST.OCF_FRAME_CD																										
			BUYER_MST.OCF_REGION_CD																										
			BUYER_MST.OCF_BUYER_GROUP_CD																										
			ORDERABLE_END_ITEM_SPEC_MST.CAR_SERIES																										



We framed this Query:
select 
  two.POR_CD ,
  two.PROD_MNTH, 
  two.PROD_WK_NO,
  sum(two.REQTD_ORDR_QTY),
  tbwou.FEAT_CD,
  trwol.OCF_BUYER_GRP_CD,
  trwol.OCF_REGION_CD,
  tbwou.CAR_SRS,
  tbwou.OCF_FRME_CD
  from TRN_WKLY_ORDR two
              inner join TRN_BUYER_WKLY_OCF_USG tbwou on 
                              two.POR_CD = tbwou.POR_CD 
                          and two.OSEI_ID= tbwou.OSEI_ID 
                          and two.PROD_MNTH = tbwou.PROD_MNTH 
                          and two.PROD_WK_NO = tbwou.PROD_WK_NO 
              inner join TRN_REGIONAL_WKLY_OCF_LMT trwol on 
                              trwol.POR_CD = tbwou.POR_CD 
                          and tbwou.PROD_MNTH = trwol.PROD_MNTH 
                          and tbwou.PROD_WK_NO = trwol.PROD_WK_NO
                          and tbwou.CAR_SRS = trwol.CAR_SRS 
                          and trwol.FEAT_CD = tbwou.FEAT_CD
              inner join MST_POR_CAR_SRS mpcs on 
                              mpcs.POR_CD = tbwou.POR_CD 
                          and tbwou.CAR_SRS = mpcs.CAR_SRS                         
                          where 
                                  two.POR_CD =:porCd and
                                  two.PROD_MNTH =:prodMnth  and
                                  two.PROD_WK_NO = :prodWkNO and
                                  trwol.OCF_REGION_CD = :ocfRgnCd and
                                  trwol.OCF_BUYER_GRP_CD = :ocfByrGrpCd and 
                                  mpcs.CAR_GRP = :carGrp and
                                  mpcs.CAR_SRS = :carSrs and 
                                  trwol.FEAT_CD in :featCd;
								  
								  
								  
	 Instead of the query framed in the Designed Document, we can use the above query to get the REQTD_ORDR_QTY from the TRN_WKLY_ORDR.
								  
								  We will map with the TRN_BUYER_WKLY_OCF_USG to get all the feature of OCF and CCF. 
								  
								  Juat Clarify.

column7: S028:Upload Issues(Indicus_376)
column47:
1.When user is not uploading any excel file.Suppose user is uploading .txt(or any other file format than excel) file.Then error message needs to be corrected.

Expected:Relevent error should be shown in above cases.

7.When more than 7 digits ocf limit qty  is uploaded then grid is shown blank from next prod months onwards  for all features as well as for that specific prod month for that feature. So,in this case appropriate error message should be shown.

column7: B000031 - Data Extraction Issue
column47:
Hi,

1. Data Extraction for Process 2.1 if Plant_Line_Summary = Y
   Data is not extracting successfully. 
Reason : Production Day No in Daily OCF Limit Trn table, Data type is Char(2). While passing Prod_Day_No = '1', Condition is not satisfied and failed to extract the record and batch is getting stopped.

Query:

SELECT DISTINCT SUM(OCF_LMT_QTY), PROD_MNTH , PROD_WK_NO ,  CAR_SRS ,OCF_REGION_CD ,  OCF_BUYER_GRP_CD ,FEAT_CD ,OCF_FRME_CD  ,length(LINE_CLASS) , 
length(PROD_PLNT_CD) , length(PROD_DAY_NO)  from TRN_DAILY_OCF_LMT
  where  CONCAT(PROD_MNTH,PROD_WK_NO) >= '2015112'  
  and POR_CD = '91'  and OCF_REGION_CD = 'G'  and
  PROD_PLNT_CD = '10'  and LINE_CLASS = '6000'  and
  PROD_DAY_NO = '1' 
  GROUP BY  PROD_MNTH , PROD_WK_NO , CAR_SRS ,OCF_REGION_CD ,  OCF_BUYER_GRP_CD ,FEAT_CD ,OCF_FRME_CD ,LINE_CLASS ,PROD_PLNT_CD ,PROD_DAY_NO;

2. In Process 2.1, we have condition (If OCF_Region_CD_Batch_Input_Parameter is Not Null). 
   So, my understanding is, we can execute the batch with or without passing Input parameter OCF_Region_CD.
   While executing the batch without OCF_Region_CD, batch stopped. Requesting for OCF_Region CD.

column7: Confirmation regarding reports of S087 - Monthly Order/Allocation Download (Fixed Format) screen
column47:
Confirmation is regarding following reports.
  1. End Item Comparison report
   2. Production Order Vol report 

In requirement document and in current implementation also , its specified that 
    1 End Item Comparison report is created using MONTHLY PRODUCTION ORDER TRN data and MONTHLY PRODUCTION SCHEDULE TRN data.
    2 Production Order Vol report is created using MONTHLY PRODUCTION ORDER TRN data.

 


 But as you know, Monthly Production Order data(which is sent to plan) is first created and transmitted at the timing of Final Order (#1)
    And Monthly Production Schedule data is first received after  the  Final Order#2 completion. 
 
Confirmation Point is :
   So this screen reports will be generated only after Final Order 1 and Final order 2 respectively if we follow above logic.
   But we ( myself,Mohan) think that these reports will be created using User inputted Orders ie. MonthlyOrderTransaction data.
   So we confirmed with GSV regarding same but as they are also not sure, Imai san told us to check data source of these reports from NMT,NMIPL OTD JPlans system.
    Same data source need to be used in Dragon also.
    
Can you comment regarding above confirmation point if you know already or can you please check NMT,NMIPL OTD JPlans system to confirm this point. 
You can refer my communication with Imaisan in below mail trail if required.

column7: B000021-End of Draft Order -When Batch is executed with Close option -Batch stops until manual modification is done in MST_LCK_CONFG
column47:

The Batch 21 is executed with input parameters as below:
sh B000021.sh 01 N N D1 C Y

Batch got failed with error as below:
90 : b000021: There is no LOCK INFO available in LOCK CONFIGURATION MST-Table for the 01 , D1
2016-02-24 10:51:13 INFO  CommonUtil:675 - stopBatch - Batch Stopped.

As per Design document the value of STAGE STATUS CODE should be "C" in MST_LCK_CONFIGURATION for Batch21 execution in End of draft order.
But as per flow if we come at End of Draft order stage - still the value of STAGE STATUS CODE is "O". Hence the batch was failing.
Is it Design issue? Or how it should be? User will not modify the DB table manually know? Please confirm.

Log files for both error and success after manual modification is attached for reference. Please check.

Suppose there are 10 OSEI_ID(Color) of one End Item and few of them but not all, are abolished for period of current OTBM~Last Production Month. So currently, in this case that record is grayed out.

This is our understanding but what logic is actually used? Please let us know.

Current Query :

column7: commit-interval setting of Batch/Interface is unclear whether it's proper
column47:
Batch and interface programs have setting of "commit-interval".
Commit-interval means database update will be committed per number of commit-interval records.
Commit-interval can be set for each function.

The Basic Design does not define the value of commit-interval.
Then it is not clear whether current commit-interval implementation settings are appropriate.
Every batch and interface commit-interval must be confirmed.

column7: B000002- OEI Buyer creation is wrong
column47:
OEI Buyer table has created additional combination of SPEC & buyer ID records which is not available in MST_END_ITM_SPEC data.

SELECT a.POR_CD,
  a.PROD_FMY_CD,
  a.PROD_STAGE_CD,
  a.APPLD_MDL_CD,
  a.PCK_CD,
  a.SPEC_DESTN_CD,
  a.ADTNL_SPEC_CD,
  b.BUYER_CD
FROM MST_OEI_SPEC a,
  MST_OEI_BUYER b
WHERE a.OEI_SPEC_ID=b.OEI_SPEC_ID
AND NOT EXISTS
  (SELECT POR_CD,
    PROD_FMY_CD,
    PROD_STAGE_CD,
    APPLD_MDL_CD,
    PCK_CD,
    SPEC_DESTN_CD,
    ADTNL_SPEC_CD,
    BUYER_CD
  FROM MST_END_ITM_SPEC c
  WHERE a.POR_CD     =c.POR_CD
  AND a.PROD_FMY_CD  =c.PROD_FMY_CD
  AND a.PROD_STAGE_CD=c.PROD_STAGE_CD
  AND a.APPLD_MDL_CD =c.APPLD_MDL_CD
  AND a.PCK_CD       =c.PCK_CD
  AND a.SPEC_DESTN_CD=c.SPEC_DESTN_CD
  AND a.ADTNL_SPEC_CD=c.ADTNL_SPEC_CD
  AND b.BUYER_CD     =c.BUYER_CD
  AND a.OEI_SPEC_ID  =b.OEI_SPEC_ID)

column7: Lot-1 B000008 Create Monthly Order Base Data: Buyer Group extraction condition is unexpected
column47:
Execute B000008, tables below was created.

TRN_NSC_CNFRMTN_MNTHLY
TRN_NSC_FRCST_VOL

Those records should be created for Buyer Group and Car Series which used by Spec data.
As we expected, SQL below can extract such Buyer Group and Car Series.
Executing the SQL, it extracted only 2 Buyer Group.
But B000008 created TRN_NSC_CNFRMTN_MNTHLY and TRN_NSC_FRCST_VOL for a lot of Buyer Group.

select
  distinct
  trn_mnthly_ordr.por_cd,
  trn_mnthly_ordr.ORDRTK_BASE_MNTH,
  trn_mnthly_ordr.prod_mnth,
  mst_buyer.buyer_grp_cd,
  mst_oei_spec.car_srs
from
  trn_mnthly_ordr,
  mst_buyer,
  mst_oei_spec,
  mst_oei_buyer,
  mst_osei,
  mst_por,
  mst_por_car_srs
where
  trn_mnthly_ordr.por_cd = mst_por_car_srs.por_cd
  and trn_mnthly_ordr.ordrtk_base_mnth = '201508'
  --and trn_mnthly_ordr.prod_mnth in ('201508', '201509', '201510')
  and mst_osei.osei_id = trn_mnthly_ordr.osei_id
  and mst_oei_buyer.oei_buyer_id = mst_osei.oei_buyer_id
  and mst_oei_spec.oei_spec_id = mst_oei_buyer.oei_spec_id
  and mst_oei_spec.car_srs = mst_por_car_srs.car_srs
  and mst_oei_spec.prod_fmy_cd = mst_por_car_srs.prod_fmy_cd
  and mst_por.por_cd = mst_por_car_srs.por_cd
  and mst_buyer.prod_region_cd = mst_por.prod_region_cd
  and mst_buyer.buyer_cd = mst_oei_buyer.buyer_cd
  and trn_mnthly_ordr.SUSPENDED_ORDR_FLAG = '0'
order by

column7: Lot-1 B000008 Create Monthly Order Base Data: Extracting LATEST MASTER SCHEDULE is wrong.
column47:
Execute B000008 with parameters below.(Create MONTHLY ORDER TRN from LATEST MASTER SCHEDULE.)

POR_CD : 01
UPDATE_ONLY_FLAG : N
OVERLAP_MS_QTY_FLAG : Y
PRODUCTION_ORDER_STAGE_CD : 10

To extract source of MONTHLY ORDER TRN data, following SQL is executed.
(From log file.)

SELECT
  t.POR_CD,
  t.PROD_MNTH,
  COUNT(t.PROD_ORDR_NO),
  t.OSEI_ID,
  t.POT_CD,
  m.FRZN_TYPE_CD
FROM TRN_LTST_MST_SHDL t
LEFT JOIN MST_OSEI_FRZN m
ON (m.FRZN_PROD_MNTH           = t.PROD_MNTH)
WHERE t.PROD_MNTH              = '201508'
AND m.POR_CD                   = '01'
AND t.POR_CD                   = '01'
AND m.FRZN_ORDR_TAKE_BASE_MNTH = '201508'
GROUP BY t.POR_CD,
  t.PROD_MNTH,
  t.OSEI_ID,
  t.POT_CD,
  m.FRZN_TYPE_CD 
;

According to the Basic Design's "Note 1" sheet, following points are different between actual and design.

1.
Design:
OSEI FROZEN MASTER should be related to OSEI MASTER by OSEI ID and month.

Actual:
OSEI FROZEN MASTER is related to OSEI MASTER by only month.
So if even one frozen record exists, all OSEI will be frozen in the month.

2.
Design:
Production months after Order Take Base Month should be target.

Actual:
Production month same to Order Take Base Month will be target.

Clarification on OCF Buyer Group Code and OCF Region Code

========
BUYER GROUP   Define which M-OCF belongs to each Market Region. Maybe it can be same as 'MAPS SYMBOL' defined in plant system.  JPN 3 CHAR 
OCF REGION CD (MAPS SYMBOL)   This is 1 digits(symbol) for OCF Region.
For example, GOM is 'G' and NE is '#'. J 1 CHAR 
OCF REGION DESCRIPTION   Description of OCF REGION CD (MAPS SYMBOL)
